race.comment: JARRITO (8) talented filly who lived up to stable expectations when resumed for a sharp victory over 1100m at Gosford. Expect to see her graduate quickly this campaign. Go close. NESRINE (1) lightly raced mare who held off all rivals to remain undefeated in two starts this time in. Up sharply in weight and can play a leading role again. LEANTOTHEMOON (4) comes out of a decent rating contest after finishing strongly at her second run back when fourth over 1000m at Gosford. Claim helps and gets map favours. SPICE BABY (10) sound return at her first run back when covered ground up on the speed for a gritty third over 1100m at Gosford. Strips fitter and not to be underestimated.
